                <div class="post-content">
                    <p>Filters transform data in DiSyL templates. Learn about all available filters and how to use them effectively.</p><h2>Security Filters</h2><h3>esc_html</h3><p>Escape HTML entities to prevent XSS attacks.</p><p><code>{item.title | esc_html}</code></p><h3>esc_url</h3><p>Sanitize and escape URLs.</p><p><code>{item.link | esc_url}</code></p><h3>esc_attr</h3><p>Escape HTML attributes.</p><p><code>{item.alt | esc_attr}</code></p><h2>String Filters</h2><h3>truncate</h3><p>Truncate text by character length.</p><p><code>{item.excerpt | truncate:length=150,append="..."}</code></p><h3>wp_trim_words</h3><p>Truncate text by word count.</p><p><code>{item.content | wp_trim_words:num_words=20}</code></p><h3>strip_tags</h3><p>Remove HTML tags.</p><p><code>{item.content | strip_tags}</code></p><h3>upper / lower</h3><p>Convert case.</p><p><code>{item.title | upper}
{item.title | lower}</code></p><h2>Formatting Filters</h2><h3>date</h3><p>Format dates.</p><p><code>{item.date | date:format="F j, Y"}</code></p><h2>Filter Chaining</h2><p>Combine multiple filters:</p><p><code>{item.content | strip_tags | truncate:length=100 | upper}</code></p>
